Very great food. I was in the mood for Thai food all week. I was walking to parking lot and found this Gem on my way. Walked in tried something I never had before, and it was a burst of flavor. Thanks for hitting the spot.
Very good, authentic pad Thai. Veggie egg rolls were also wonderful! Food was hot even after my walk home. Large portions; I had the pad Thai for 2 meals.
thai food, mmm, delicious. Everyone at our table was very satisfied. Service is consistently above par. The prices are good for what you get. Similar to a cafe in Las Vegas I loved.
My top spot for Thai food. Very delicious. The bill was reasonable.
thai food and service at this spot is very good. Stopped in on a Monday I think. Next time I'll be back with my coworkers.
Fine location for quality Thai food. there was fast, efficient, and courteous service. the place has a good feel to it.

It is located on the basement of the the building. Shared with Friends sushi. People sometime missed pickup their orders lol. I love their Basil dish and Thai pepper steak. Yes they are the most popular dishes here! You should try the Chives dumpling which you can't find it anywhere in town!
Excellent spot for tasty Thai food. Food was so delicious. Atmosphere is similar to a place in Columbus I loved.
It was a big portion to eat. It was very delicous, but the menu said it was spicy, but I found it to be quite mild. The price was okay!
Thai food, yeah, quality stuff. I was so stuffed. I see why this place has so many good reviews.

A fav spot for delicious Thai food. I wish there were more places like this around town. The staff was very kind and attentive. The bill was appropriate for the quality. Food is similar to a cafe in Indianapolis I loved.

I ordered from their website but I was told that I have to use grubhub. Nothing against grubhub but I was interested in the small business keeping all their profits so I tried to see if they would deliver. They said they would and mentioned that it would be a $4 fee + tip so I agreed to that hoping to give the delivery guy an amazing tip in order to promote local businesses. When the delivery person arrived to my building he said I have to pay $10 preset tip or else he would leave. I had no choice but forcefully pay the $10 tip! This is not what I expected, it was extortion from a small business. Lesson learned, trust the big companies that have a set few. At least you know what you are paying for
Good food. Really good value for money deal.
I love this place. The staff is friendly and the food is good. Great neighborhood Thai food.

Faulty technology resulted in dozens of  grub hub users not to get thier order. The day I was there there were at least six or seven couriers from GrubHub waiting because the restaurant didn't put the clients' orders in the system and thus the kitchen didn't make the food. This caused a backlog which means the people who are in the restaurant had to wait even longer to get their food because of this error. Furthermore the staff was not kind to the GrubHub couriers even though they were just doing their job. One of the couriers had a minor language barrier and instead of explaining the situation in a different manner he just became more frustrated and repeated the same thing. All the other staff was perfectly nice.
Excellent and authentic dishes! Recommend the Nam Tok.

Silver Spoon is the best Thai food I’ve ever had in Chicago! We order out about once a week, the food is always ready when we arrive and everyone is SO NICE! Our favorites are the Pad Thai with Tofu, Tom Yum soup (SO SPICY), and the chicken fried rice.
This place is worth trying. They serve large portions for affordable rates. Always well organized and with fantastic ambience. Highly recommended.

My new addiction. I recently moved downtown and had to find a new Thai place. I couldn’t be happier that this was my first attempt. Silver Spoon is delicious! I LOVE their Massaman chicken curry! I could eat it for every meal. They are so attentive to special requests (peanut allergy in the group) and the food is always to delicious. They give great portions and the leftovers heat up perfectly the next day tasting just as good.
Nice spot for thai food. I will be bringing family next time. Feels like a place in Los Angeles I loved.
Good Food & prices aren't bad.
The food is Awesome, fresh and fulfilling. I eat their all the time.
Fantastic service great food will be back
Amazing Pad Thai noodle with Tofu. Highly recommend to go try their food. I definitely will return!
I truly think I’ve tried at least 50 Thai places in the city and by far, silver spoon is the best. Great dishes, good potion sizes, and amazing taste!
Wouldn't accept tap to pay even though they had the terminal.

Yesterday was the first time we visited this good restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last. We enjoyed the evening a lot with the efficient service, with the high quality  dishes and fine drinks and with the decent pay. We will absolutely return there again.
Consistently not great pad Thai. Some dishes are good.

Awful experience. Ordered Silver Spoon set to be delivered around 7 pm, and around 7:30 became worried that it hadn't arrived. Called the store, and they said it had been dropped off around 6:50 and the delivery man and my doorman had called me, and they left it at the front desk. The driver didn’t call me, as I had no missed calls around the time the order was said to be delivered. Also, our front desk never called either, and I know that because when I went downstairs to get the food, I asked our doorman if they called to let me know the food arrive, and they said they didn’t, so off the bat there, the delivery man wasn't being truthful. Our doorman told us that the delivery man told them that I had been contacted and would be coming down, so the story the delivery man told Silver Spoon management doesn't add up. The issue was two fold in that the food was cold, and rice sitting out for over and hour by the time we got to the front desk isn't sanitary, and I'm immunocompromised, so would have requested the delivery man come straight to our door. The night of the order, Silver Spoon refused to help and begrudgingly told me they would give me a refund and to go through Chowow, but when ChowNow went to them to confirm the refund, the restaurant refused. They also were incredibly unprofessional, yelling at me on the phone and saying the issue must be on my end, when I initially called to ask about the delivery process.
Small clean restaurant easy to find on foot. Staff acknowledges you right away and is super friendly. Food comes out hot and tasty. Great lunch specials.
Awesome!
Was ok. Not much more to say really. The young coconut drink was great. Not their fault but I wanted roasted duck. Should have investigated more.
Very tasty and good value
I love spicy 🌶
Very delicious! Sweet and sour mango chicken was so good.
Solid food and fast service. Will keep going back.
Very good value for the food and very good service. Thank you!
Favorite Thai restaurant in Streeterville. Great lunch deal.
Everything is always hot and fresh. Not that expensive,worth every dollar.

At the first moment  you arrive in this place  team give you a good feeling. Very friendly crew, it is a friendly restaurant to go out with buddies or with your date. Excellent  cooking, qualified  chef, honest  price and professional  service. Highly recommended.
Pretty good food. The atmosphere was a little gloomy, but for the price it was fine.
I usually order the lunch special which allows for noodles or rice. Also spring rolls and egg rolls. Good food and reasonable price.
I constantly come grabbing some food in here. I enjoy the speedy customer service and well made food. Kudos.
Pad Thai lacked flavor and barely had any chicken in it. The Spring rolls were raw spring rolls, I had to end up giving them to a friend & my friend even said it was nasty.
Loved it

Love a good Thai food place that’s tasty and not too costly. First picture is the papaya salad that I asked for spicy. Boy, was it spicy! Nothing unbearable but def helped clear my sinuses. The other picture is of my chicken pad Thai which you can never go wrong with. Overall, would recommend to come here if your looking for cheap, delicious eats!

Very nice thai restaurant. I loved food. It's not as cheap as looks, but the food was delicious. So whatever it takes. It's hard to find. First I went upstairs but it's a whole different restaurant with sushi. This one is downstairs in the basement.

I like to go with friends to this place with my highest recommendations. I visit this place often. This recommendation is always successful. The meals are yummy and the stuff is generous and cooperative. Every time  we visit this place we enjoy a cheerful evening.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.

I ordered takeout. The staff was very friendly. However the food was unfortunately not great. The spring rolls were made with the wrong kind of dough. The panang curry was like a paste. Almost like peanut butter. My boyfriend and I doctored it up with more spices and liquid to make it more like actual curry. Also, there were no vegetables in it. It was only chicken and sauce. Don’t think I’ll be back.
The food was very fresh and excellent. Friendly customer service. Will definitely come again when back in Chicago!!!
I was rally surprised how good the food was. The workers are super nice and it was cheap and sooo delicious! I tried the Pad Thai with chicken and it was the best I ever had! Hope to come back once
Great Thai food for less price. The food is very authentic .
the best curry noodle i've ever had (and i've had a lot), i HIGHLY HIGHLY recommend this place.
Very tasty and very affordable. This place made me a Thai food fan
The thai noodle soup was very delicious, just the same as I tasted in Bangkok. The dessert mango sticky rice was fresh and delicious too
Reasonable priced Thai restaurant. Food was good and service was fast.
The food is very gucci famsquad.

Low key atmosphere in the heart of downtown. Family run business; great food, the most delicious iced tea, and very well portioned entrees perfect for 2 or for a small family dinner! Limited seating but worth any wait time!
BBQ pork over rice

Very nice and cheap too

Silver Spoon Thai restaurant is in the basement, inexpensive and service is good. The food is pretty good not great, but considering the price, it’s absolutely fine. We all three enjoyed our meals. Would I go back?  If was right near there probably.  Would I  seek it out? Probably not.
Amazing😊

This was the best meal we had on our two week US holiday. Som tam, red curry, spicy fat rice noodles all delicious. The mild chicken curry was much enjoyed by our little girls too. First class, friendly and excellent value.
Really good food in casual setting.

I saw the sign on their door that said "Best Thai" and naturally, it attracted us! I love Thai food so we gave it a try. I love how it was underground! It's a cute, simple place. Nothing fancy. The food wasn't that good. It was unseasoned and just did not taste good. I was disappointed. I expected a little heat or spice but it was bland! Even their dumplings! Kind of disappointing from a place that's so highly rated. Oh well.

We   Are new to the neighborhood and went online to look for Thai restaurants around I could deliver. Silverspoon came up in the results and we decided to order from them from their website. Our order came over two hours after we ordered even despite contacting the restaurant via the phone. Sadly the food was just mediocre. There was not much flavor let alone space in any of the dishes. We will not be ordering from this restaurant again.

This place was suggested to me as the best Thai food in the neighborhood I was in at the time and it didn't disappoint. Although the spring rolls were a little different, they were still full of flavor. The Tom Yum vegetable soup was delicious ànd the Spicy crispy Basil noodle were amazing!!! I will definitely come back the next time I'm in Chicago.

Great food! I'm from Singapore and have been trying to find a good pad thai in the US for so long and this is the first one I've had that meets my standards.

The food was delicious, and priced great! Our hotel was around the corner and we ate here twice.  The papaya salad, Tom kha, and beef pad see eww was delicious l, and our plates went back empty.  Fast service, with patio and indoor, underground seating.  Mom and pop vibe.

Excellent food!! The Thai iced tea was the best I've ever had. The red curry was extremely flavorful. The curry fried rice was amazing!! As you can tell from the picture we finished everything. Excellent place for vegetarians.
Excellent Thai food near the consulate's office.  Super taste and very reasonably priced for Chicago Thai restaurant!!!

Best Thai food I have found living in Chicago. Red Curry is phenomenal and plenty of vegetarian friendly options. Excellent food and service and prices are fantastic ~$10-12 for a curry is great in the city and it is filling.

Food was really good. It truly is a hidden spot! Go if you want some good food at a nice price.

I love this place hidden in a basement. The food is delicious authentic Thai. The lunch menu is inexpensive. The service is fast, professional and friendly. I love the pad Thai, the spicy basil leaves, and the Thai curry. The restaurant is small, and you may have to wait - definitely worth it!
Excellent service. Good prices. Nice atmoshpere. I liked the service. The beef was well cooked. The portions we're good. The fried rolls were worth it
Decent food for the price. Its in a basement so not the best ambience. Good place for delivery.
Food is good.  Service is slow but then the wait is worth for that food.
Great service, delicious authentic Thai food!  Loved the baby egg rolls as a starter along with the egg salad.  The main course, Red Chicken Curry was phenomenal!  Will definitely be back!

Delicious Thai Food in Chicago! The wonton soup was fabulous. Pad Thai and pad see ew were also fantastic. Quality stuff. Nice quaint, low-key place with friendly staff.

great thai food, it has to be since it is next to the Thai Cousulate.

I’ll admit apprehension due to Yelp’s reviews. I am glad I ignored them.  I almost walked past this little place while on an adventure in Chicago. I am so glad I did not miss it. They had all the traditional fare but each dish I had provided some unique flavors and I am now a huge fan of the Thai custard that was recommended.  The atmosphere is casual and cozy and the staff had smiles for every encounter.  Overall this was a delightful experience and I’m leaving with a full tummy and a smile.

The food here was delicious. So much so did not even bother with a picture of our food. Service was extraordinarily fast. Food came out fast and piping hot. We will definitely have to stop here again when we are in the area. Authentic, delicious, fast plus byob what else can you ask for

Amazing flavors and extremely well priced. I ordered the Pad Talay #510 and it tasted amazing. One of the top Thai seafood dishes I have had. The service is very quick as well. I will definitely make this a must-stop when coming to visit Chicago again.

Great Thai food! Their iced Thai coffee was delicious too!

Just passed through Town on a visit from Canada, Ordered Pepper steak and chicken Pad thai to go, Our Bus was parked directly opposite to this establishment, and decided to try it out! Food was Mediocre at best! I was truly disapointed being Asian! I have tasted better food at mall Kiosk's, Pepper steak was watery,and the meat was a few small Shreds of beef ,white in color. A very lovely Thai place with amazing food! The food always arrives very quickly & the service is great! Definitely would recommend their curries or spicy eggplant / cashew chicken entrees.

I was referred here by the nearby T-Mobile store and was not disappointed!  They recommended a great dish with chicken, broccoli and peanut sauce.  You can always tell a place is great when it's small and at mealtime fills to overflowing!  Will be back next time I'm in town.

Probably my favorite Thai place in the city and I eat a LOT of Thai. I knew it would be special when I saw it was not only in a basement and next door to the Thai Embassy. To succeed there you know it’s gotta be special and it is.

I found this restaurant on accident and it rocked my world! A gem amongst the busy chains in the city, great prices and wonderful food. The intimate atmosphere helps give this a small home-y kitchen feel. Highly recommend!

This is a lovely Thai restaurant. Visiting around this time of winter (late December) has become somewhat of an annual tradition. Nothing like hot and spicy food to warm you up in cold winter weather! They serve a variety of delectable dishes. I would warn that the place may have a bit of a smell to it at times, something pungent from the spices, but don't mind it. The food tastes delicious! Also, value is top-notch. More than worth the price!
Really tasty food. Good quality food close to Michigan Avenue, that's unusual. I am sure, we will come back.

The food was good but my curry sauce/flavor was not very strong. It tasted more like a peanut sauce than anything else. The tofu was cooked well but the dish had zero vegetables it was just tofu and noodles. Also, the crispy noodles were only crispy on the edges and still gooey in the center. It was BYOB which is nice but I would recommend asking questions about the dishes before ordering.

We got carry out. They didn't give us one of the dishes we ordered and paid for. One of the other dishes we ordered was beef green curry - they gave us chicken. Pad Thai and pineapple fried rice was bland. The Northern Thai sausage was so spicy, it was inedible (and I'm from Asia so I'm used to spicy food!). Disappointed. We didn't bother going back to ask for the dish they missed since we didn't rate the ones we did receive.

I've only been here once while visiting town for a conference. I asked for the drunken noodles, which I wanted spicy, and they were pretty good. I was disappointed a bit because they definitely served them mild. Don't know if they messed up the order or gave me American spicy i.e. not spicy at all. I'd suggest making the staff know that you legitimately want some spicy food if that's what you really want.  Just make sure that if you're in a big party that you either make sure they can divvy up your bill when you order or bring cash. We were with a big party (three families) and it took awhile for them to figure out who ordered what when it came time to pay the tab.

We stepped in and sat down and waited.  We're given menus and waited.  3 couples and 1 gentleman were the only ones in restaurant.  A couple came in and sat down and were actually waited on before us and also orders taken.  We finally were able to order.  We both ordered diet coke, one without ice.  They deliver in a can so don't expect any refills as they charge even more.  We ordered a chicken rice soup and 10 minutes egg rolls to start.  We watched the other couple that sat down after us enjoying their meal while we were ordering.  That's how long this was taking.  We ordered red curry entree and a beef entree.  Portion sizes were small considering other restaurants.  The red curry is listed as bei g spicey, NOT.  The red curry came in a bowl like a soup and was so bland it was like eating milk.  Mini egg rolls were not bad.  Chicken rice soup wasn't bad.  Both entrees were lacking in Thai flavor.   The place is also quite filthy.  They have tiles coming up on the restaurant floor and a badly fix job of other tiles.  Another couple were also complaining about the food while were eating.  There is way to many restaurants close to this one and way better Thai than this one.  I do not recommend this restaurant as a place to even try.  Don't waste your money.  Go to some of the other establishments and spend your good hard earned money.  Worst meal I have had in years.  She also wouldn't give me a breakdown of how she came up with the price.

great food!!

I recommend the pad Thai! Wish there was a better price for brown rice substitution over white rice on plates that serve it.

Good food and reasonable prices. Pad thai noodles a bit mushy and over cooked but other dishes fine. Staff extremely friendly. This comes highly rated in the tourist mags or online. Not big into Thai food but this place was great!

Nice, tucked away Thai restaurant serving all of the familiar Thai dishes. We go there because they are very friendly with my 4-year-old daughter. They gave her some candy bars for her birthday. And the lunch time prices during the week are really cheap for a downtown location.
On time good food

Fantastic food. I had the vegetable noodles and tofu soup and they bother we’re phenomenal. Don’t hesitate when ordering front this place!! You won’t be disappointed. Fresh vegetables and tasty pasta made this meal great.
Pretty authentic
Delicious food at an inexpensive process in an expensive area. Very nice staff and food was made quickly.
Delicious and great prices!

I've been coming here for a good few years and I have yet to have anything less than a great experience. The service is great and the food is consistently good (the panang curry is fantastic). I drag all of my friends here when I'm in town, regardless of their meal preferences. If I'm in the city, I go to Silver Spoon before I leave, no exceptions.

Ordered for delivery. Food took over 90 minutes to arrive and was cold. Even worse, the driver marked the order as delivered at around an hour. Food was average at best. Chicken felt like leftover bits instead of meat. The order was correct at least.
Very nice waiting staff. My pad see eiw was okay and usual. Decent prices especially in this location.

Favorite take-out Thai place. Fast service (20 minutes max) and amazing food. Get the basil chicken and the vegetable rolls!
Spicy. Fresh veg and decent meat. Quick service.

TLDR; subpar service offset by the best black pepper spice ever tasted on beef.  Summary: Had papaya salad, Tom Yum soup, black pepper beef, sticky rice, and iced Thai teas. Came here at about 6 PM on a Saturday with a Thai companion.  Companion did the ordering in Thai. Food was authentic, but portions were some of the smallest from any Thai establishment experienced, with the soup having little substance, the rice being dry, and the salad plain. The black pepper on the beef really did it, though. Don't know what was used - would have it again anytime!  The service was noticeably absent. Long times to order, receive food (other tables that ordered after were being served first), lacking drink refills, and having to go up to the wait staff to get the ticket (the table next to ours grabbed the same staff member who brought our ticket to get theirs).  + Authentic food + Best beef spice + Price - Service - Proportions - Time - Seating / Facilities
